data.description: Mountain and equestrian living blend perfectly on this stunning 34+ acre property. Equestrian features include a 9-stall barn with a tack room and living quarters, a large paddock, a newly seeded fenced pasture with water, arena, and trails through the forested acreage of the property. There is also a large workshop right next to the barn, making all your farm projects that much easier! The stunning home was designed to provide wonderful views to the surrounding scenery from almost every room. You'll enter to be greeted by a large dining area, sitting room, and glass doors open to a truly serene back porch setting with a peaceful water feature. Adjacent to the dining area, you'll find a butler's pantry turned sports bar, the perfect place to catch the big game. The chef's kitchen looks into the family room and offers granite countertops, custom cabinetry, and an oversized island. The main floor is bolstered by a large living room area with an impressive two-story stone fireplace. This cozy yet spacious space is made to feel even larger by the adjacent glass-enclosed porch. The porch and the deck that it opens up to offer fantastic views of this southern tip of the Blue Ridge Mountain Range. Around the house, there is plenty of room for gardening, not to mention a fenced yard for your pets. The basement offers a second kitchen, perfect for the baking enthusiast as it comes with an island and Viking Range. Whatever you create in the basement can be loaded straight into the car, as there is access to the three-car attached garage. Away from the home, barn, and pasture, there are still acres of mature woods to explore. Whether you love hunting, birding, or just a good nature walk, wide trails take you through the trees and down to a creek at the edge of the property. This property offers a little something for everybody, not to mention the potential to add even more magic! Come see it and experience this unique North Georgia equestrian estate.
